# CVE-2026-32274 — black 22.3.0 arbitrary file write in cache handling
# Added: 2026-04-16
# Re-review: 2026-07-16
# Justification: black is not an installed dependency. The flagged file is
#   spaCy's bundled test fixture at .venv/lib/python3.11/site-packages/spacy/
#   tests/package/requirements.txt. This requirements.txt is reference data
#   for spaCy's own internal package tests; it is not parsed, installed, or
#   executed by any code path in this project. The vulnerable black version
#   is never loaded into our process.
# Upstream: spaCy ships test fixtures in its production wheel. A long-term
#   fix is to file an issue with spaCy requesting test/ exclusion from the
#   production distribution.
CVE-2026-32274
